In this article, President Trump makes several remarks during a press conference on the South Lawn. He mentions that he is considering various options regarding TikTok and the potential sale of the company. He expresses his disagreement with FBI Director Christopher Wray on issues such as China and Antifa. President Trump also discusses the possibility of reopening the border with Canada and praises the USMCA trade deal. He defends his administration's response to COVID-19 and criticizes Joe Biden's handling of the swine flu pandemic. The President asserts that the US has done a phenomenal job with respect to COVID-19 and highlights the advancements in therapeutics and testing.